    • Method Detail

      • initialize

        public void initialize()
        This method is called when GenerateReports window is being created.

        Its purpose is to add listener to the clientIdCheckBox. If it is selected, the clientIdBox is set as enabled and the user is allowed to choose a clientId from the list.

        The reportList is populated with all items in the ReportType enum class. The clientIdList is populated with data retrieved from the database with use of H2Database.getClientIdData() method.

        See Also:
        CheckBox, ComboBox

      • getReportParams

        public ReportParams getReportParams()
        This method creates a new ReportParams object with the parameters selected in the reportTypeBox and clientIdBox.
        Returns:
        ReportParams object with data needed for creation of the report.
        See Also:
        ReportParams
